14:
You mean... The company declared
you dead, right?
18:
Yes... They took care of everything
after the incident. It didn't even
make the news...
21: I see. It must suck being dead...
24:
B-but it looks like the company also
gave lots of money to my family...
Like workers' compensation,
insurance, hush money...
27:
It all equaled out to about ten times
the amount I got with my loan... Isn't
that generous?
34:
Yeah, I bet my parents are happy
about it tooâ€”the money, not my
death.
36:
Now that 3MM's looked after my
family, that means I'm free, right? I
can finally start over...
40:
So it's time to live life on my own
terms!
50: What is there even for me to do?
54: Got plenty of time to kill, huh.
58:
Y-yes... I'm just standing around
minding my own business.
Marveling at this world's blue skies...
61:
But I was just thinking, what can I
even do while I'm here? The only
thing I'm good for is doing chores.
65:
*gasp* A m-mutant?! ...Oh wait, no.
You're... Nimbus, was it?
68:
Hmph. I'm going to pretend that I
didn't just hear that.
71:
Anyways. You're getting bored with
chores, was it?
75: Y-yes, I mean... I'm not complaining!
78:
I'm just envious that all of you get to
prove yourselves in battle... When
will I ever be ready?
80:
I just want to see some action... I
don't just want to be on the sidelines
this whole time...
87:
Some "action", huh? Can't you just
smack some of that cybernetic stuff
on yourself and get battle-ready?
90:
I'm not built for that sort of thing...
Plus, it costs a lot of credits.
93:
And I'm not talking about looks
either, battle upgrades don't come
cheap. Speaking of which, my right
arm is still on loan...
98:
If money's the issue, then how about
earning some right now?
102:
Come on, let's see what you're
made of!
108:
Stop slacking off! Focus on the next
target!
113:
I need to reload! G-give me five
seconds!
127:
Ahaha. Better than standing around
all day, right?
131:
I think that was TOO much
excitement for one day... Where do
you even find the energy?
136:
We all start somewhere, don't we?
Anyhow, here's your half of the
reward!
141:
Wh-what? But you did most of the
work... That wouldn't be fair to you.
144:
Quit your whining! Just shut up and
take the money.
150:
Then tonight's meal is on me. You
really helped me out back there!
155:
Heh, now there's something we can
agree on! There's this super fancy
new place I've been dying to check
out.
160:
H-have mercy! You didn't give me
THAT much!
